To reproduce all panels in this figure you need to download the raw counts data (raw_counts_kallisto.tab) from the GEOXXXX. Clinical data is needed to reproduce this Figure but is only available from the corresponding author upon reasonable request. In this script the Clinical Data is stored in an object named âClinical_datâ.

###Load the kallisto counts data
kallisto_counts<-read.delim("raw_counts_kallisto.tab") #Path were you stored this file
##Columns are the patients and rows the genes in (Hugo_symbol)

##Load clinical data (Only available upon request)

Clinical_dat$ID<-Clinical_dat$Anonym_ID
##Normalize expression data using Deseq2
library(DESeq2)
##Put in the same order...
kallisto_counts<-kallisto_counts[,order(factor(colnames(kallisto_counts), levels = Clinical_dat$ID))]#reorder names

table(colnames(kallisto_counts)==Clinical_dat$ID)#safety check, all must be true

rownames(Clinical_dat)<-Clinical_dat$ID
###Import to Deseq2 to normalize data...
##This is only to generate the matrix of vst counts...(condition is taken from mutation category but can be other)
library(DESeq2)
DESEq_tmp <- DESeqDataSetFromMatrix(countData = kallisto_counts,
                                        colData = Clinical_dat[,c("ID","RECIST_R_nR")],
                                        design = ~ RECIST_R_nR#This design is only to make the function work but wont be used to get differentially expressed genes at this point
                                    ) 

DESEq_tmp

##Run deseq2

dim(DESEq_tmp)

keep <- rowSums(counts(DESEq_tmp)) >= 1
table(keep)
DESEq_tmp <- DESEq_tmp[keep,]

dim(DESEq_tmp)

dim(DESEq_Bionikk_vst)
##Export vst normalized data...

saveRDS(DESEq_Bionikk_vst,"DESEq_Bionikk_vst.rds")

library(DESeq2)
DESEq_tmp <- DESeqDataSetFromMatrix(countData = counts_kallisto_AB_TLSpos,
                                        colData = Clinical_dat_AB_TLSpos[,c("ID","RECIST_R_nR")],
                                        design = ~ RECIST_R_nR)

DESEq_tmp

##Run deseq2

dim(DESEq_tmp)

keep <- rowSums(counts(DESEq_tmp)) >= 1
table(keep)
DESEq_tmp <- DESEq_tmp[keep,]

dim(DESEq_tmp)

#check design
design(DESEq_tmp)

#dds_tmp<-estimateSizeFactors(DESEq_taqman, type = 'iterate')

dds_tmp <- DESeq(DESEq_tmp)
##Extract results
res_H_L <- results(dds_tmp, alpha=0.05,contrast=c("RECIST_R_nR", "NR", "R"))
#This comparison means that a fold change positive is more expressed in NR; and a foldchange negative is less expressed in R
#
resLFC_all<-as.data.frame(subset(res_H_L )[,c(1:2,5,6)])
resLFC_all$baseMean<-rownames(resLFC_all)
colnames(resLFC_all)<-c("Gene","log2FoldChange","pvalue","padj")
resLFC_all <- resLFC_all[order(resLFC_all$pvalue,decreasing = F),]

write.table(resLFC_all,file="Bionikk_TLSposAB_NRvsR_n58_FC_allvalues.tab",row.names = FALSE, quote = FALSE,sep = "\t")


###Check gaba releted genes
Signatures_GABA<-Manual_signatures[1:4]
resLFC_all[resLFC_all$Gene%in%unique(unlist(Signatures_GABA)),]

####Check differentially expressed genes crosslink with GABA from deseq2 #######
GABA_reduced_Bionikk<-lapply(Signatures_GABA, function(x){
  intersect(resLFC_all$Gene[resLFC_all$log2FoldChange>0&resLFC_all$padj<0.05],x)
})
GABA_reduced_Bionikk2 <- unique(as.character(unlist(GABA_reduced_Bionikk)))
GABA_reduced_Bionikk2

#"GNAI1"  "ADCY2"  "GABBR1" "APBA1"
#save signature
saveRDS(GABA_reduced_Bionikk2,file = "GABA_reduced_Bionikk2.rds")
#
library(ggplot2)



###############Create the Volcano plot for panel b #############################################
# Create a dataframe from the gene list
df <- data.frame(log2FC = resLFC_all$log2FoldChange, pvalue = resLFC_all$padj)
rownames(df)<-resLFC_all$Gene
###Easiear plot with EnhancedVolcano
library(EnhancedVolcano)
##To change coloring...
keyvals.colour <- ifelse(
    abs(df$log2FC) < 0.25 | df$pvalue>=0.05, 'gray',
      ifelse(rownames(df)%in%GABA_reduced_Bionikk2, 'darkred',
        ifelse(df$log2FC>=0.25&df$pvalue<0.05, 'firebrick1',"royalblue")))

keyvals.colour[is.na(keyvals.colour)] <- 'gray'
  names(keyvals.colour)[keyvals.colour == 'gray'] <- 'Not sig.'
  names(keyvals.colour)[keyvals.colour == 'darkred'] <- paste0('GABA related genes (n=',length(GABA_reduced_Bionikk2),")")
  names(keyvals.colour)[keyvals.colour == 'firebrick1'] <- paste0('Enriched in NR (n=',table(keyvals.colour)["firebrick1"],")")
  names(keyvals.colour)[keyvals.colour == 'royalblue'] <- paste0('Enriched in R (n=',table(keyvals.colour)["royalblue"],")")

p_volcano_bionikk<-EnhancedVolcano(df,
                lab = rownames(df),  # Use gene names as labels
                x = 'log2FC',         # Specify log2FC column
                y = 'pvalue',        # Specify p-value column
                #xlim = c(-5, 5),     # Adjust x-axis limits if needed
                title = "Differentially Expressed Genes NR vs R"
                ,pCutoff = 0.05,FCcutoff = 0.25,
                #legendLabels=c('Not sig.','Log2FC','padj','padj & Log2FC'),
                colCustom = keyvals.colour,
                legendPosition = 'right',legendLabSize = 16,legendIconSize = 5.0,
      drawConnectors = TRUE,
    widthConnectors = 0.75,
    selectLab = c(GABA_reduced_Bionikk2,"IGHG1","IGHG2","CD68","CD163","CXCL2","CXCL5","CXCL9") ##Only label genes of interest...
    ,labFace = 'bold',boxedLabels = TRUE,
    pointSize = c(ifelse(rownames(df)%in%GABA_reduced_Bionikk2, 5, 1))
    ,colAlpha =c(ifelse(rownames(df)%in%GABA_reduced_Bionikk2, 1, 0.1))
    ,xlim = c(-3, 3),ylim = c(0,5))

p_volcano_bionikk
ggsave(p_volcano_bionikk,filename = "VolcanoPlot_27NR_vs_31R_gabaGenesSelection.pdf",width = 14,height = 10)

#Needed objects from panel c:
#Clinical_dat_AB_TLSpos with the GABA_Bionikk calculated
#Clinical_dat_AB_TLSpos$GABA_Bionikk
##Needed function
plot_contingency<-function(data,
           variables = c("x", "y"),
           hide_legend = F,
           text_size=6,
           create_labels = T,
           inverse_factor2=F,
           order_factor=NULL,
           palette = NA,
           test_name = c("chisq.test", "fisher.test")[1],
           labs = c(xlab = "",
                    ylab = "",
                    legend_title = ""),
           hide_test = F,
           title = ""){
    if(inverse_factor2){
      data[,variables[2]] <- factor(data[,variables[2]],levels=rev(levels(data[,variables[2]])))
    }
    cont_table <- table(data[,variables[1]],data[,variables[2]])
    #clean data table to avoid empty rows
    non_empty_rows <- rowSums(cont_table)!=0
    cont_table <- cont_table[non_empty_rows,]

    if(create_labels){
      #sapply(levels(factor(data[,variables[2]])), function(x) paste(variables[2],x,sep="_"))
      colnames(cont_table) <- sapply(levels(factor(data[,variables[2]])), function(x) paste(variables[2],x,sep="_"))
      rownames(cont_table) <- sapply(levels(factor(data[,variables[1]])), function(x) paste(variables[1],x,sep="_"))
    }
  if(test_name != "fisher.test" & test_name != "chisq.test"){
    stop("incorrect test, valid options are fisher.test or chisq.test")
  }
  if(test_name == "fisher.test"){
    error_test <-  if(class(try(fisher.test(cont_table),silent=T)) == "try-error"){
      test_res <- fisher.test(cont_table,simulate.p.value = T)
    }else{
      test_res <- fisher.test(cont_table)
    }
  }
  if(test_name == "chisq.test"){
    test_res <- chisq.test(cont_table)
  }
  #make sure there is a matrix (enough values in both sides)
  if(!is.null(dim(cont_table))){
    cont_table_perc <-apply(cont_table,1,function(x) {
      res <- x / sum(x) *100
    })
    cont_table_m <- melt(cont_table_perc)
    cont_table_m$Var1 <- factor(cont_table_m$Var1)
    p <- ggplot(data=cont_table_m, aes(x=Var2,y=value,fill=Var1,label=value))
    p <- p + geom_bar(stat="identity",width=0.95)
    #to reverse order of bars
    #p <- p + geom_bar(stat="identity",width=0.95,position = position_stack(reverse = TRUE))
    p <- p + geom_text(label = paste0(as.vector(t(cont_table)),"\n(",format(cont_table_m$value,digits = 1),"%)"),
                       position = position_stack(vjust = .5),size=text_size)
    p <- p + theme_minimal()

    if(any(!is.na(palette))){
      p <- p + scale_fill_manual(values = palette)
    }
    #p <- p + theme(legend.title = element_blank())#,axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 25, hjust = 1))
    p <- p + guides(fill=guide_legend(title=labs[3]))
    if(hide_test){
      p <- p + labs(subtitle=paste("p = ",format(test_res$p.value,digits=3),sep=" "),title=title,x=labs[1],y=labs[2])
      if(test_res$p.value < 0.05 ) p <- p + theme(plot.subtitle=element_text(face="bold"))
    }else{
      p <- p + labs(subtitle=paste(test_name, " p = ",format(test_res$p.value,digits=3),sep=" "),title=title,x=labs[1],y=labs[2])
      if(test_res$p.value < 0.05 ) p <- p + theme(plot.subtitle=element_text(face="bold"))
    }

    if(hide_legend){
      p <- p + guides(fill=FALSE)
    }
  }else{
    p <- ggplot()
    test_res <-1
  }
  return(list(p,test_res,cont_table))
